            <h3>Kidapawan City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Climb Mt. Apo. It is the City’s major tourist destination. It has two climbing season. January to June is highlighted with an organized climb during summer time specifically during Holy Week. October to December is being highlighted with an organized climb on October during semestral break when students are given the chance to enjoy the season.</li>
                <li>2. Avail of package tours like visiting two falls with bat caves and trekking activity.</li>
                <li>3. Tour fruit farms. It is usually done during peak season of ripening and harvest time of fruits.</li>
                <li>4. Visit flower farms where ornamental plants, materials and plants used for landscaping and bonsai are all available.</li>
                <li>5. Participate in various events and festivals for the whole year round like the City’s foundation anniversary, The Timpupu Fruit Festival, The Pangavukad Flower Festival, Kanyon Kawayan Festival, Festival of Lights, Children Festival, Culinary Festival and October Fest.</li>
